The paper deals with the stability and synchronization of networked systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of decentralized and distributed controls suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The study of networked systems and synchronization is also relevant to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The use of compensators and estimators suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper's focus on synchronization in networked systems suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
